<!--increment n attribute for ms containing multiple ms items-->
                  <summary>These two paper leaves are bound together with <ref type="extant_mss"
                          target="http://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/MS-ADD-01042-00002/1">Add.
                        1042.2</ref>: <quote>These specimens were sent over from Nepal by Dr D.
                        Wright in 1873, when it was proposed to obtain copies of various Sanskrit
                        manuscripts existing in Nepal, for the University Library. It was from these
                        leaves that the whole of the present collection took its rise</quote>
                     (Bendall 1883: 26-7). They contain part of the <title xml:lang="san">Maitrakanyakāvadāna</title>, the last story from the <title xml:lang="san" type="other">Divyāvadāna</title>.
                  </summary>

                  <msItem n="1" defective="unknown">
                     <title xml:lang="san">Maitrakanyakāvadāna</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="san">Sanskrit.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
